When #Apple is earning $6 Billion from India in 22-23 - #Reliance is launching affordable laptops. But Why?  Often I have seen that Indian companies always try to build cheap and sell cheap to so called Indian consumers. They justify by saying we know what Indian customer needs.   Apple is tapping the Indian market in billions. Many phone makers in past kept on making and selling cheap phones but look an average person in India who is holding #smartphones in their hands.   If you build a good product, people take loans, they wait in queue for hours to pay you even if they can't afford the product they will find ways to afford it.   It is understandable that we have to make products for every segment of the customers but why Indian companies never bet on premium products and capture the market?
